<br>
Level 9: Light Healing<br>
Level 8: Renew Elements<br>
<br>
Level 19: Healing<br>
Level 20: Renew Summoning<br>
<br>
Level 51: Superiour Healing<br>
Level 52: Transon's Elemental Infusion<br>
<br>
Level 60: Nature's Touch<br>
Level 60: Transon's Elemental Renewal<br>
<br>
However, these spells are similar in level only. The odd thing is that Renew Elements is more efficient than Renew Summoning until Level 50.<br>
<br>
I would suggest that Renew Elements was changed from a max 50 point heal at level 25 to a max of 33 at Level 18.<br>
<br>
Then changing Renew Summoning from a 220 heal at Level 60 to a 100 point heal at Level 30, reducing the manna cost from 100 to 60.<br>
<br>
I would also add a new spell at Level 29 which emulates Greater Healing:<br>
<br>
Transon's Elemental Mending.<br>
Level 29 Heal for 300<br>
150 manna<br>
<br>
With this thinking, we sacrifice short-term healing efficiency for greater quantity heals.<br>
<br>
Of course, I don't hold any grandious hopes that this will actually happen, but I think it's not a bad idea. What does everyone else think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(6/7/02 4:29:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=234.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Re-adjustment of pet heals?</span><hr size=1> I don't know about your exact numbers, but I agree that some intermediate pet heal is needed.  Have you ever looked at the Beastlord spell line?  I did for the first time last night, and was amazed at all the pet heals they get.  They get them almost every level!  Now for them, it is like our every 2nd level, but still, nothing from lvl 20 until 50+ is rather bad.<br>
<br>
The should just put a new pet heal in at 34 or 39 to make a smooth progression.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp.<br>
 <p>Eriol Telcontar - Dragons Revolt<BR>
Magician of the 44th Summoning<BR>
The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 257<br> <font color=#333333>(6/8/02 8:36:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=234.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Re-adjustment of pet heals?</span><hr size=1> My feeling is we either need our pet heals to match the efficiency of beastlords, or the line replaced. At lower levels I seem to recall playing pet cleric worked ok, but at my level (56) it is always more efficient to simply summon a new pet than keep one healed up. I've gotten to the point where I don't bother with trying to get max con pets (unless they are light blue, I keep'em), I'll just chain pets since it's less mana than trying to keep them alive via our pet heals.<br>
<br>
Consider the 51 earth pet, 300 mana to summon, ~3k hitpoints.<br>
<br>
With Transon's it'd take 5 heals to bring it from the brink of death to full health. At  275 mana a pop that is 1450 mana, for 300 mana I get a new pet at full health, 150 mana to cast burnout on it, and 175 for cadeu of flame, total cost, 625 mana. That's less than half the mana needed to keep a pet alive through heals, and the amount of heals needed is actually optimistic from my experience.<br>
<br>
Only time i use the heals anymore is when farming greenies and the pet occasionally needs a boost so I don't have to wait on it's regen. The only other use I have for the line is removing slows.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uomegasyphon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#333333>(6/8/02 3:53:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=234.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  comment</span><hr size=1> personally id like to see some type of pet only regrowth or regen hp type spell. like transons elemental regrowth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#333333>(6/8/02 7:57:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=234.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Pet regen</span><hr size=1> I had the same idea, but pets regen very quickly already at 30hp/tick. If we were given a short-term duration like 18 ticks with a heal effect of 300ish/tick (scaled from 29-52, of course) that would be useful, however with such a short duration, an instant heal would do just as good.<br>
<br>
That and the Level 60 heal whould be GREATLY increased! I'd even say should DOUBLE. 1,800 hps for 400 manna isn't that bad for a pet-only spell - kind of like all the effects of the Burnout series crammed into only 150 manna. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(6/9/02 4:06:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=234.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Good idea, but...</span><hr size=1> A new pet heal isnt really needed IMHO. As Kinelaria pointed out, it is a lot more efficient to summon a new pet instead of trying to COMPLETELY heal the pet. I remember fighting seafuries at low 50's and just using two lvl 20 heals during the fight plus one small nuke to shorten the way they run when done <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But then, why would you want to do to completely heal your pet anyway? The only reason to use a heal would be to keep the pet alive for a few moments so it can finish a fight. And for those purposes, the pet heals we get are sufficient. When a fight is over you can let your pet regen while you med. If you can keep your pet through fights by using ONE (or TWO) heals, do it. If you need to heal more, it would probably be better to summon a new pet instead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also it isnt really fair to compare our heals to the beastlord pet heals, since their class is built around those spells. They cant finish fights quick as we can (with nukes), and they cannot summon new pets as easily as we can. So they need to have efficient and good heals.<br>
<br>
So my take is, use heals when it CAN save you the trouble to make another pet. If you have the higher (lvl 52) heal, you should also consider if you could not shorten the fight by using 250 mana rather on a nuke instead of a heal <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
