<br>
This style suited me well, as for 54 levels I had a stable but laggy modem connection which made chain casting pets too risky, and by the time I got DSL, I was set in my ways.  It was a slow but steady style, which worked well studying XML or Java between pulls, and also become the foundation of my grouping style, which is to invite others to a mastered solo camp, and increase the pull rate based on group attendence.<br>
<br>
However, with the recent pet changes, I have been experimenting with what I call <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Deferred Chaining</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that is, one pet per fight, reclaiming the pet <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>after</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the fight is over, not before.  With this method I have much less down time, and the experience rolls in.<br>
<br>
Even under this circumstance, though, I find pet heals useful to conserve mana.  Sometimes I run up against a string of stronger than average spawns against weaker than average pets, and my mana bar is down some.  In this case, the 52 pet heal costs less mana than a nuke, but buys more time for the pet.  That is, TEI gives my pet about +20% health.  However, by the time amount of that a 1K nuke shortens the fight, the pet would take about 10% damage.  Since I am no longer concerned about outdamaging the pet, the heal, in this case, is a better choice, even though I am chain casting.  Better yet, since the pet ends with fight with a little more health, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Reclaim Energy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> yields a little more mana.<br>
<br>
I do note that there appears to be a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;soft spot&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of relative weakness in the career of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in the 30's, and a new pet heal at 29 might well add a little bit of needed backbone.  I do not see how it would hurt much.<br>
<br>
In any case, I think it best that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be allowed a choice of styles, and not forced into <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chain Casting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> by necessity.<br>
